# ğŸ”§ **Deployment Strategies (Super Easy)**

### **1ï¸âƒ£ Rolling Deployment**

Old version ko step-by-step replace kiya jata hai.
**Real-life:** Room ka paint ek-ek wall ka karte ho, pura room ek sath nahi.

---

### **2ï¸âƒ£ Blue/Green Deployment**

Blue = old version
Green = new version
Green test ho gaya â†’ traffic shift
**No downtime**

**Real-life:**
Naya flat ready ho jata hai â†’ shift â†’ puraani jagah band.

---

### **3ï¸âƒ£ Canary Deployment**

New version pehle 10% users ko
Successful â†’ 100% users ko

**Real-life:**
Restaurant new dish pehle thode customers ko serve karta hai feedback ke liye.

---

### **4ï¸âƒ£ Recreate Deployment**

Old version stop â†’ new version start
Downtime hota hai.

**Real-life:**
Computer restart karke new software install karna.

---

# ğŸ—ï¸ **Deployments in Kubernetes**

Kubernetes me Deployment ek controller hai jo ensure karta hai:

* correct number of pods running
* correct version running
* automatic rollback
* automatic scaling

Command:

```
kubectl create deployment myapp --image=nginx
```

Update image:

```
kubectl set image deployment/myapp nginx=nginx:latest
```

---

# ğŸ“¦ **Deployment vs Release (Very Clear Difference)**

**Deployment = code server pe chala diya**
**Release = users ko visible ho gaya**

Kabhi kabhi deploy hota hai but feature off hota hai (feature flags).

---

# ğŸ§µ **Simplest One-Liner Definition**

**Deployment = when your application becomes live and usable for real users.**

